input.plan:
# Fix Arrow Z-Index Layering in WorkflowHeroAnimation

## Problem Identified
The arrow gets cut off by adjacent elements because all three grid sections (left, center, right) have no explicit z-index, causing them to stack in DOM order. The ShootingPosts component's positioned elements (source card with `z-index: 1` and flying duplicate cards) can overlay the arrow.

## Solution: Add Z-Index Layering

### Add CSS Rule for `.workflow-hero-arrow` (after line 333)
```css
.workflow-hero-arrow {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 100%;
  position: relative;  /* Create stacking context */
  z-index: 10;         /* Elevate above adjacent sections */
}
```

### Optionally: Set Z-Index for Sections (defensive approach)
Add rules for side sections to establish clear stacking order:
```css
.workflow-hero-section--source {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}

.workflow-hero-section--destination {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}
```

## Result
- Arrow will always render **above** source card and flying duplicate cards
- Arrow will always render **above** destination platform cards
- Maintains proper visual hierarchy: arrow on top, cards below
- No impact on animation performance

